  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "To clear your Hotmail inbox, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign in to Hotmail (Outlook.com):**\n   - Go to [Outlook.com](https://outlook.live.com) and log in with your Hotmail credentials.\n\n2. **Select Emails:**\n   - In your inbox, you can manually select individual emails by clicking the checkbox next to each email.\n   - To select multiple emails, click the checkbox at the top left corner of the email list to select all visible emails.\n   - If you need to select all emails in your inbox, you can click \"Select all\" or similar option (depending on the interface).\n\n3. **Delete Emails:**\n   - Once the emails are selected, click the \"Delete\" button, which is usually represented by a trash can icon. This will move the selected emails to the Deleted Items folder.\n\n4. **Empty Deleted Items Folder:**\n   - To permanently delete the emails, go to the Deleted Items folder.\n   - Click the option to \"Empty folder\" or select all emails in the Deleted Items folder and press \"Delete\" again to permanently remove them.\n\n5. **Sweep (Optional):**\n   - You can use the \"Sweep\" feature to quickly move or delete multiple emails from specific senders or older than a certain date. This can help with clearing out bulk emails without manually selecting each one.\n\n6. **Archiving (Optional):**\n   - If you prefer not to delete certain emails but want to clear your inbox, you can archive them. Select the emails and choose the \"Archive\" option to move them to the Archive folder.\n\nRemember to regularly check and clear your Junk or Spam folder as well to keep your inbox manageable.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to clear your Hotmail inbox effectively.",
